General distribution. This species is distributed in western and central Europe, northward to southern Finland (
Rassi et al . 2015
) but is yet unknown from Byelorussia , and northern and central parts of European Russia (Nikitsky 2008); it is however common in Poland (
Kubisz et al . 2014
).

Earlier records. This species was found in Mažeikiai ( Monsevičius & Pankevičius 2001 ) (KZM), and Neringa districts (
Ivinskis et al . 2009
) (NRC).
